content:
Unfortunately most browsers don't accept any other methods besides `GET` and `PUT`. Because of this you need to intercept form output. In jQuery this is done with the following script:

``` javascript
$(function(){
    $('#form_id').submit(function(e){

        var serial = $('#form_id').serializeArray();

        var out = {};

        for (var i = 0; i &lt; serial.length; ++i){
            var s = serial[i];
            out[s[i].name] = s.value;
        } // end for

        $.put('/rest/url', out, function(data){
            // process response
        }); // end put
    })

});
```

With Underscore this can be more tersely expressed:

``` javascript

$(function(){
    $('#form_id').submit(function(e){

        var serial = $('#form_id').serializeArray();

        var out = _.reduce(serial, function(hash, field){
            hash[field.name] = field value;
            return hash;
        }, {});

        $.put('/rest/url', out, function(data){
            // process response
        }); // end put
    })

});

```

You'll need a more advanced filter to interpret array form data.
